# GStack Engineering Rules

## Workflow

- Scene A (Large Features): CEO Review → Eng Review → Pause for approval → Code → Module review → Global review
- Scene B (Bug Fix): Trace bug chain → Systematic root cause → Fix → Build verify
- Scene C (UI Tweak): Locate component → Precise edit → User confirms
- Scene D (Refactor): Review target → Small steps with build verification → No business logic changes

## Quality Gates

- Zero silent failures: every catch block has user-visible feedback
- State completeness: every loading state has loaded/error counterpart
- Empty states: every list/table has empty state message
- Interaction feedback: every button has loading/disabled/animation response
- DRY: extract after 3+ repetitions
- No residuals: no console.log, no TODO, no hardcoded paths
- Type safety: no `any` type, complete interface definitions

## Design Quality

- Style consistency: follow project design system
- Restrained animation: only enhance UX, no flashy effects
- Responsive: all grid layouts degrade gracefully
- Accessibility: hover and focus styles on all interactive elements
